  "title": "Admin Assistant",
  "description": "<ul><li>Perform administrative duties</li><li>Provide support to various departments and operational teams</li><li>Plan and execute company events or activities</li><li>Provide support for special projects</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties assigned</li></ul><p><br />Admin</p><ul><li>Research required information</li><li>Source for new vendors and suppliers</li><li>Liaise with vendors and suppliers</li><li>Perform comparison and analysis</li><li>Data entry</li></ul><p><br />HR</p><ul><li>Maintain employees’ leaves, medical and attendance record</li><li>Computation of casual labour pay and CPF contributions</li><li>Act as touchpoint for HR-related matters</li></ul><p><br />Sales & Marketing</p><ul><li>Source for new event venues</li><li>Liaise with vendors</li><li>Handle queries and feedback</li></ul><p><br /><br />Requirements:</p><ul><li>Preferably with prior experience in similar role in Chinese restaurant</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office applications</li><li>Able to speak and write Mandarin/Chinese to liaise with Mandarin speaking colleagues</li><li>Willing to learn and open to taking on a variety of tasks</li><li>Team player who is able to work independently</li><li>Meticulous with an eye for details</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Able to multi-task and handle high volume of work in fast paced environment</li><li>Able and willing to work on weekends and PH when necessary</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Suitable candidates will be offered attractive salary package, bonus and other incentives.<br /><br />We regret only shortlisted applicants will be notified.</p>",
